Fabulous spring/summer dessert and while I've struggled with traditional creme brulee in the past, I had no problem achieving a perfect layer of crunchy caramelized sugar on the surface, by just using the broiler. Now two words of advice on preparation. First, I would advise placing the crust on a baking sheet PRIOR to pouring the filling in. Makes it much easier to get into the oven without making a big sloppy mess. Secondly, I would suggest covering the crust with a ring of foil prior to broiling to prevent the crust from burning. Otherwise, this is a most impressive and easy dessert recipe. Fresh summer berries and maybe a spoon of whipped cream are a must alongside.

